Install Docker (macOS)

1. xcode-select --install
   Installs required developer tools (like git, compliers, make) for Homebrew.

2. /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"
   Installs Homebrew, the macOS package manager, this pkg manager simoifies the installation of docker, git, node.js etc

3. echo 'eval "$(/opt/homebrew/bin/brew shellenv)"' >> ~/.zprofile
   Ensures brew works properly in your terminal.

4. brew install --cask docker
   Installs Docker Desktop (GUI + CLI).

5. docker --version
   Confirms Docker is installed and running.

---

 ✅ Set Up Jenkins using Docker

6. docker pull jenkins/jenkins:lts
   Downloads Jenkins LTS image from Docker Hub— pulling it ensures you can later run it in a container.

7. docker run -d --name jenkins -p 8080:8080 -p 50000:50000 -v jenkins_home:/var/jenkins_home jenkins/jenkins:lts
   Runs Jenkins container with web UI on port 8080 and saves data.

8. docker exec -it jenkins cat /var/jenkins_home/secrets/initialAdminPassword
   Gets the initial admin password to unlock Jenkins.

9. docker ps
   Verifies Jenkins container is running.

10. Open in browser
    Go to http://localhost:8080 to set up Jenkins.
